From 8653d9a1c152bdafaf2d7b4c15881aca54ab6c93 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Sanket Bumb <sanket@yourowncrm.com>
Date: Sun, 14 Jun 2026 04:17:51 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] fix: location dropdown, booking warnings, audit logging,
 location color bands
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Appointment dialog:
- Location search dropdown: fixed missing position:relative wrapper that
  caused the dropdown to render incorrectly / be invisible
- Location field now shows ALL locations on focus (not just first 10)
- Location pre-fills correctly when editing an existing appointment
- Audit Logs button: closes appointment dialog first, reopens centered
  (same fix pattern as Visit Notes — was rendering at page bottom)

Booking conflict warnings (all overridable via 'Book Anyway'):
- DOUBLE_BOOK: resource or staff already booked in this slot
- OUTSIDE_HOURS: appointment time is outside resource working hours
- SAME_PATIENT_SAME_DAY: patient already has an active appointment that day
- Backend AppointmentRequest: allowDoubleBook / allowOutsideHours flags
- Backend now SKIPS the corresponding check when the flag is true,
  so 'Book Anyway' actually succeeds on save (previously it always
  re-threw BusinessException regardless of the flag)
- Frontend: errors from checkAvailability are now surfaced in the
  dialog instead of leaving it silently open with no feedback
- AvailabilityConflict: added conflictType + overridable fields

Location color bands on schedule grid:
- Now computed for BOTH resources AND staff (previously resources only)
- Z-index fixed: bands(0) < hour-row grid-lines(2) < appointments(5)
  bands render behind appointments, hour-rows are transparent so
  bands show through
- Border uses solid location color, fill uses ~16% opacity overlay
- Tooltip shows location name + time range

Backend logging (logback-spring.xml):
- Rolling file appender: logs/yourowncrm.log (10MB/daily rotation,
  30-day retention) — auto-recreates file if deleted while running
- Separate AUDIT logger -> logs/audit.log (90-day retention)
- SERVER_STARTED / SERVER_SHUTDOWN events
- LOGIN_SUCCESS / LOGIN_FAILED (with reason: bad_password, locked,
  deactivated, tenant_not_found, user_not_found) / ACCOUNT_LOCKED
- LOGOUT endpoint (POST /api/auth/logout) + frontend call on logout
- BUSINESS_RULE_REJECTED for caught BusinessExceptions (e.g. blocked
  double-bookings before this fix)
- UNHANDLED_EXCEPTION with full stack trace for uncaught errors
- Fixed Logger import collisions (java.util.logging vs slf4j)
  in UserServiceImpl and GlobalExceptionHandler
